            <p><strong><a href="http://www.forbes.com/sites/kathleenchaykowski/2016/11/11/facebook-to-ban-ethnic-affinity-targeting-for-housing-employment-credit-related-ads/" target="_blank">Facebook to Ban ‘Ethnic Affinity’ Targeting for Housing, Employment, Credit-Related Ads After Criticism from Lawmakers</a></strong></p>
            <p>Facebook recently announced that it will no longer allow advertisers to target employment, housing, and credit-related ads posted on the social network by “ethnic affinity.” The ban comes after widespread pushback from lawmakers, the media, and civil rights leaders in the US over the potential discriminatory effects posed by such restrictions.</p>
