            <p><strong><a href="https://techcrunch.com/2016/11/17/linkedin-is-now-officially-blocked-in-russia/" target="_blank">LinkedIn is Now Officially Blocked in Russia</a></strong></p>
            <p>LinkedIn has run afoul of a Russian law that requires all websites to store Russian users’ personal data on servers located in the country. As a result, Roskomnadzor, Russia’s communications regulator, has begun enforcing a country-wide block of LinkedIn. While Google and Apple have reportedly complied, both Twitter and Facebook still appear to be storing their data associated with Russian users outside of Russia.</p>
